title: Aaron Peskin trades vinegar for honey in race for supervisor
text:
Photo: Paul Chinn, The Chronicle Aaron Peskin hands out campaign literature to voters on Jackson Street in Chinatown in San Francisco, Calif. on Thursday, Sept. 17, 2015. Peskin is seeking to unseat incumbent Julie Christensen in District 3 on the Board of Supervisors, a position he previously held from 2001-2009. Sitting at a large wooden desk in his office on Columbus Avenue, former and maybe future Supervisor Aaron Peskin received a Google alert of his name in a new article.
